        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer106360273" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9374077184060959211">This is an elegant and romantic retelling of the ballad of Thomas the Rhymer, a harper who was taken by the Elven queen to spend seven years in Elfland and came out with the gift of telling only the truth. I was somewhat unsatisfied with the events of the novel, and with the character of Thomas himself, who was sufficiently self-centered that I had a hard time sympathizing with him, but the language was beautiful, as Kushner&apos;s always is, and it was overall a good read. </span>
  <span id="freeText9374077184060959211" style="display:none">This is an elegant and romantic retelling of the ballad of Thomas the Rhymer, a harper who was taken by the Elven queen to spend seven years in Elfland and came out with the gift of telling only the truth. I was somewhat unsatisfied with the events of the novel, and with the character of Thomas himself, who was sufficiently self-centered that I had a hard time sympathizing with him, but the language was beautiful, as Kushner's always is, and it was overall a good read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9374077184060959211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

