<div id="review_3196757881" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3196757881" />
    <a title="Karen Poremski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/108085992-karen-poremski"><img alt="Karen Poremski" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3196757881?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen Poremski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen Poremski" href="/user/show/108085992-karen-poremski">Karen Poremski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3196757881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11346339258710377357">Things I liked about the novel: <br/>-- the plot unfolds via the voices of several characters (not just one), and those voices are wonderfully vivid;<br/>-- the descriptions of the living spaces and... well, THINGS around the characters helped to convey important details about their way of living and seeing the world;<br/>-- I feel like I learned a lot in a fairly small space about the world of faerie in the old stories;<br/>-- I found the characters sympathetic, even when I didn&apos;t like them all that much.<br/><br/>Things I </span>
  <span id="freeText11346339258710377357" style="display:none">Things I liked about the novel: <br />-- the plot unfolds via the voices of several characters (not just one), and those voices are wonderfully vivid;<br />-- the descriptions of the living spaces and... well, THINGS around the characters helped to convey important details about their way of living and seeing the world;<br />-- I feel like I learned a lot in a fairly small space about the world of faerie in the old stories;<br />-- I found the characters sympathetic, even when I didn't like them all that much.<br /><br />Things I didn't enjoy:<br />-- I was a bit confused sometimes about the "rules" in the world of faerie, and about the relationships of characters in that world to each other. But this may have had more to do with my cognitive state (due to chronic illness) rather than the writer's work.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11346339258710377357" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


